		  theory which covers the summarization and description of
		  theoretical probability distributions, the summarization
		  and description of observed data samples, estimation of
		  parameters and quantiles of probability distributions, and
		  hypothesis tests for probability distributions. The theory
		  involves such established procedures as the use of order
		  statistics and Gini's mean difference statistic, and gives
		  rise to some promising innovations such as the measures of
		  skewness and kurtosis described in section 2, and new
