		  and show that it could suffer, on average, more than four
		  major losses a year. The bank had seven losses exceeding
		  hundreds of millions of dollars among its 52 documented
		  losses of more than US$1 million over the 1994-2004 period.
		  The tail of the loss distribution predicts that this bank
		  is in danger of experiencing extreme operational losses
